Distribution.
Central Paratethys. Late Badenian (middle Miocene, Serravallian): 
Carpathian Foreland Basin
: Biłka, Czepiele, Hołubica, Jasionów, Morozicha, Olesko, Poczajów Stary, Podhorce, Szuszkowce, Tarnoruda, Turówki, Werbów, Żabiak, Zalisce, Zapadnia (
Ukraine
) (
Hilber 1882
; 
Friedberg 1909
, 
1914
), Bochnia, Niskowa (
Poland
) (
Niedźwiedzki 1886
; 
Bałuk 1970
) (see 
Nosowska 2019
for a map of the localities). Eastern Paratethys. Tarkhanian to Konkian (middle Miocene): Don Basin: Novocherkassk (
Russia
), Krynka river in Azov region; Northern Caucasus region: Dubrovaya; Southern Caucasus: 
Azerbaijan
, 
Georgia
; Transcaspian region: Kara-Bogaz-Gol in 
Turkmenistan
(
Popov 1986
; 
Bogachev 1905
).
